      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIN CITY BANDIT (2) has a strong winning strike-rate over this track and trip with two wins and a placing from six tries. Scored by 5.5 lengths last time (42.03) in a Mix over 720m at this track. Looks a key chance on best form. WHISKEY GRACE (7) finished fourth last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 570m at Temora, taking a Grade 4/5 in an exceptional 32.68. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. GO JO JO (8) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 720m behind SIN CITY BANDIT (43.50) in a Grade 5. The form out of his last race has been franked. Expected to feature in the finish. ANCIENT EGYPTIAN (1) warrants respect although new to this distance.",
